Here is the complete, detailed implementation plan for the PulseBoard channel plugin.

## Implementation Plan: PulseBoard Channel Plugin

### Summary

Seven new files in `extensions/pulseboard/`, zero modifications to existing files. The plugin follows established OpenClaw extension conventions, using Nostr as the closest reference but simplified to stubs since PulseBoard is fictional. It supports both `"direct"` and `"group"` chat types.

### File 1: `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

**Purpose**: Define the account configuration interface, the resolved account type, and the account resolution function.

**Contents**:

```typescript
export interface PulseBoardAccountConfig {
  enabled?: boolean;
  name?: string;
  apiKey?: string;
  boardId?: string;
  dmPolicy?: "pairing" | "allowlist" | "open" | "disabled";
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
}

export interface ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  accountId: string;
  name?: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  configured: boolean;
  apiKey: string;
  boardId: string;
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
}

export interface PulseBoardMessage {
  id: string;
  from: string;
  to: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  chatType: "direct" | "group";
}

export function resolvePulseBoardAccount(opts: {
  cfg: Record<string, unknown>;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  const channels = (opts.cfg.channels ?? {}) as Record<string, unknown>;
  const pbCfg = (channels.pulseboard ?? {}) as PulseBoardAccountConfig;
  const accountId = opts.accountId ?? "default";
  const apiKey = pbCfg.apiKey ?? "";
  const boardId = pbCfg.boardId ?? "";
  const configured = Boolean(apiKey && boardId);

  return {
    accountId,
    name: pbCfg.name?.trim() || undefined,
    enabled: pbCfg.enabled !== false,
    configured,
    apiKey,
    boardId,
    config: {
      enabled: pbCfg.enabled,
      name: pbCfg.name,
      apiKey: pbCfg.apiKey,
      boardId: pbCfg.boardId,
      dmPolicy: pbCfg.dmPolicy,
      allowFrom: pbCfg.allowFrom,
    },
  };
}
```

**Design rationale**: Single-account model (`"default"`). `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount` has `accountId: string` which satisfies the `{ accountId?: string | null }` constraint required by `createChatChannelPlugin`'s generic parameter. The `cfg` parameter uses `Record<string, unknown>` which is compatible with `OpenClawConfig` (avoiding a direct import of the config type).

